(Arnold, David O.,1991. Computers and Society Impact! Mitchell McGraw - Hill, New York, p.372):
Horce race politics.
The first is the rating game. We seem to have become number happy. In this computerized era, it is all too easy to measure quantity and think we are measuring
quality. We judge education by grade point averages and movies by the number of asterisks (or stars or some other symbols) assigned to them. The future of
television shows, beauty contest entrants, novels, and even corporations rests on the ratings. We have even been known to judge each other on a 10-point scale 
mode famous in a Bo Derek movie a few years back.